                <note rend="inline" type="source">700.00116 M. E./155</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Chief of the Division of
                        Controls</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Green</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-12-28">December 28,
                            1939</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Colonel Per Zilliacus, the Finnish Military Attaché, called me by telephone this
                    afternoon. He said that he had been instructed by his Minister to ascertain
                    whether there was any likelihood that this Government would place a moral
                    embargo on the exportation of aviation gasoline to the U. S. S. R.</p>
                <p>I told Colonel Zilliacus that the U. S. S. R. did not import aviation gasoline in
                    significant quantities from the United States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Joseph C. Green</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
